NHL ICE HOCKEY - JAGR AND LEMIEUX LEAD PENGUINS PAST ISLANDERS . Jaromir Jagr notched his league - leading 37th and 38th goals in the first period and Mario Lemeiux collected four assists as the Pittsburgh Penguins beat the New York Islanders 5 - 2 on Friday . The streaking Penguins have won six in a row and are 9 - 0 - 1 in their last 10 and 17 - 2 - 3 since November 21 . Pittsburgh goalie Patrick Lalime stopped 37 shots to remain unbeaten at 11 - 0 - 1 since being called up . Lemieux ' s third assist , coming on Jagr ' s second goal , moved him past Bobby Clark into 13th place on the all - time assist list . Lemieux , who has 854 career assists , has two goals and 14 assists in his last four games . " Our big guys just took over the game tonight , " said Pittsburgh coach Ed Johnston . " When they ' re playing like that , they ' re awful , awful tough to stop . " Jagr was a question mark , " Johnston said . " He put on a pretty good demonstration for a guy who was sick . " Bryan Smolinski and Zigmund Palffy tallied for the Isles , losers of six in a row . In Anaheim , Paul Kariya recorded his first career hat trick and added an assist to lead the Mighty Ducks to a 5 - 2 victory over the Buffalo Sabres . Kariya broke a 1 - 1 tie late in the second period with a short - handed goal and snapped a 2 - 2 deadlock with his second of the game at 4 : 36 of the third . After assisting on Teemu Selanne ' s 24th goal just 71 seconds later , Kariya completed the scoring and his hat trick with a powerplay marker at 9 : 06 of the third . Buffalo ' s Dominik Hasek made 47 saves in a losing effort as the Ducks outshot the Sabres by a wide 52 - 21 margin . At New Jersey , Tony Amonte , skating on a bruised left knee , scored with 20 seconds left to lift the Chicago Blackhawks into a 3 - 3 tie with the Devils . Denis Pederson had a powerplay goal and an assist for the Devils , who blew a 3 - 1 lead . Eric Weinrich scored to move Chicago within one with 6 : 43 left in the second period . The Blackhawks pulled goaltender Jeff Hackett in the final minute for an extra attacker and Amonte streaked into the New Jersey zone and beat Martin Brodeur with a low wrist shot for his team - leading 27th goal . In Dallas , Keith Tkachuk and Mike Gartner each had a goal and two assists to lead Phoenix Coyotes to a 4 - 3 victory over the Stars . Gartner and Tkachuk scored just under six minutes apart in the second period to put the Coyotes up 3 - 2 . Jeremy Roenick added a powerplay tally at 8 : 06 of the third , which proved to be the game winner as Phoenix snapped a three - game slide . Tkachuk , who leads Phoenix with 26 goals , has 14 goals and 22 points in his last 13 games . Nikolai Khabibulin made 31 saves for Phoenix . In Vancouver , Pavel Bure had a goal and two assists and Kirk McLean made 20 saves as the Canucks handed the Hartford Whalers their eight straight road loss with a 5 - 3 victory . Bure , back on track after a slow start , scored the game - winner in the third and assisted on earlier goals by Alexander Mogilny and David Roberts . He has a seven - game points streak with seven goals and six assits . Glen Wesley and Kevin Dineen tallied goals for Hartford , which is 0 - 6 - 1 in its last seven games . 
